paddock shepherd
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a shepherd who looks after sheep on flats and down country [as opposed to a hill shepherd or hill man who works on larger upland blocks.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
